description: A recent caste survey in Telangana reveals that Backward Classes (BC) make up 56.33% of the state's population, including BCs among minorities. Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes constitute 17.43% and 10.45% respectively. The comprehensive and unprecedented survey was conducted across 1.12 crore households.
title: Caste survey: Backward classes Telangana's largest group at 46.25%

description: Three construction workers died while repairing a sewer joint at Kolkata Leather Complex, likely due to inhalation of toxic gas. The incident occurred shortly after the Supreme Court banned manual scavenging in major cities including Kolkata. The mayor announced compensation, and an inquiry has been launched to determine accountability.
title: Days after SC ban on manual scavenging,3 die in Kolkata manhole

description: India's Deep Ocean Mission received a significant boost with a Rs 600 crore allocation for the Samudrayaan project. This initiative includes sending a manned submersible to explore ocean depths. Additionally, Rs 1,329 crore has been allocated to Mission Mausam to enhance weather and climate forecasting capabilities using advanced technologies.
title: Deep Ocean mission ‘Samudrayaan’ gets Rs 600cr budget boost

description: Former UK PM Rishi Sunak visited Parsee Gymkhana in Mumbai, marking the club's 140th anniversary. He played cricket with local boys and interacted with gymkhana members. Sunak, of Indian origin, noted the historical significance of the venue and the gymkhana's acquisition from the colonial government.
title: For Sunak, a trip to Mumbai not complete sans game of cricket
'Gender budget' touches Rs 4.5 lakh crore with 37% jump

description: Maharashtra Navnirman Sena chief Raj Thackeray emphasized the need to prioritize the interests of locals in state's developmental projects to prevent displacement and loss of cultural identity. Speaking at the Vishwa Marathi Sahitya Sammelan, he urged thoughtful land allocation and encouraged Maharashtrians to promote Marathi language and culture.
title: Infrastructure projects shouldn’t displace ‘sons of the soil’: Raj Thackeray

description: JDU's Sanjay Jha defends the Union Budget provisions for Bihar, stating it addresses long-pending demands. He highlights significant support like central aid for flood-affected Kosi region, Makhana Board for fox nut farmers, a greenfield airport, and a national agro-tech institute as major boosts for the state.
title: JDU hails Budget, says it fulfils Bihar's long-pending demands

description: Indian Railways anticipates a 16% rise in passenger revenue for the 2025-26 financial year, driven by increasing demand for AC3 class and premium trains like Vande Bharat. Passenger earnings' contribution to total revenue is expected to rise, providing flexibility for attracting more cargo.
title: Premium-train demand helps Railways project 16% revenue jump

description: A team from AIIMS Delhi visited Rajouri’s Badhaal village to investigate a mysterious illness that has claimed 17 lives. No new cases have been reported in the last nine days. Families from the affected village have been relocated to isolated centres, and the village declared a containment zone.
title: Rajouri deaths: Delhi AIIMS experts meet patients, record clinical history

description: The Indian government anticipates a slowdown in highway construction over the next two years due to fewer new project awards in 2023-24. Despite this, the road transport ministry aims to exceed its target of constructing 10,400 km of national highways this fiscal year, hoping to reach 11,000 km, though maintaining this momentum will be challenging.
title: National highways construction to slow down amid fall in award of projects
Get invigilators to wear hi-res body cam, plant jammers at exam venues: K'taka HC

description: The Allahabad High Court has expressed concern for children living in prisons with their incarcerated parents, directing the UP government to create a structured programme for these children's education, health, and development. The order came after rejecting the bail application of a woman charged with her step-son's murder.
title: High Court directs for special care of kids confined with parent in prisons
Mercedes driver hits gas instead of brake, rams into 5 at Mumbai airport

description: An Orissa HC judge has granted bail to Manas Ati, charged with electric pole theft, on the condition that he plants 200 saplings of local varieties in his village. The district nursery and revenue authority will assist in providing saplings and identifying planting locations. Ati must maintain the trees for two years.
title: Odisha HC grants bail to thief with 'sapling plants' condition

description: Indian-American economist Kshama Sawant has accused the Indian government of harassment after her e-visa to visit her ailing mother in Bengaluru was repeatedly rejected. Despite her husband receiving a visa, her own applications have been denied, potentially due to her opposition to various Indian policies.
title: PIO activist accuses government of denying visa to meet ailing mom
‘Swarm’ of 7 quakes in a week triggers panic in Uttarkashi

description: Uttarkashi district police have registered a case against unknown individuals for spreading false rumours about an impending high-magnitude earthquake. A widely circulated social media post caused panic, leading residents to leave their homes on a cold night. Efforts are underway to identify those responsible.
title: Uttarkashi quakes: Case registered against rumour-mongers

description: India and Russia aim to enhance inter-parliamentary relations with a visit to India by state duma chairman Vyacheslav Volodin this week. The visit precedes a potential trip by President Putin to India for the annual summit. Despite geopolitical challenges, India maintains robust ties with Moscow, emphasizing defense, security, and trade cooperation.
title: Vladimir Putin aide's trip to help boost India-Russia ties

description: A 22-year-old Dalit woman was found murdered after an alleged rape in Ayodhya, sparking political backlash before the Milkipur bypolls. CM Yogi Adityanath hinted at SP's involvement, while opposition parties criticized the BJP government for law and order issues. Two suspects have been detained.
title: Dalit woman's murder in UP stirs political storm before key bypoll
Drug unit run by ex-sarpanch busted in Madhya Pradesh
In migrant haven, Kerala women get hitched to 'guest workers'
Key valve in satellite launched in 100th mission suffers glitch, Isro weighing options

description: A Kerala police SIT is probing the suicide of 14-year-old Mihir Ahammed, allegedly due to bullying at GEMS Modern Academy. His mother Rajna PM claims he faced physical abuse and harassment at the school and on the bus. The school denies the allegations but has suspended the vice principal for an impartial inquiry.
title: Schoolboy ends life after brutal ragging, Kerala SIT to probe

description: In a bid to boost India's nuclear sector, Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced plans to amend the nuclear liability law and introduce a nuclear energy mission. This aims to attract foreign investment and increase private sector participation. By 2033, five indigenously developed small modular reactors will be operational, with a Rs 20,000 crore allocation for research and development.
title: 17 years after US deal, govt to clear hurdles, open nuclear power highway

description: Abhishek Sharma's remarkable 54-ball 135 led India to an emphatic 150-run victory over England, securing the series 4-1. Sharma's innings broke multiple records, including the highest T20I score by an Indian. Despite Phil Salt's quick-fire 55, England's batting collapsed, managing only 97 runs. This victory margin of 150 runs stands as India's second-largest in T20Is, following their 168-run victory over New Zealand in 2023.
title: 5th T20I: Abhishek's record-breaking 135 powers India to 4-1 series win vs England

description: Rebecca Lobach, the third pilot involved in the Blackhawk helicopter crash with an American Airlines plane, had her identity withheld due to her family's request. The crash, which resulted in no survivors, is under investigation. Conservative commentators claimed that her identity was withheld initially because her family was erasing her social media history.
title: Was Blackhawk pilot's name kept secret for a reason? Here's what we know

description: Palmer Luckey, founder of Oculus and Anduril, criticizes US media for overhyping Chinese AI startup DeepSeek's claims about their low-cost AI training models. Luckey challenges the $5 million training cost figure and emphasizes the need for scrutinizing such claims to avoid damaging US companies.
title: ‘DeepSeek's $5m number is to hurt US & there are lot of idiots who…’

description: Trinamool Congress leader Shatrughan Sinha visited Delhi to support Aam Aadmi Party leader Atishi in her Kalkaji Assembly constituency campaign. Amid AAP and Congress tensions, Atishi accused BJP of using money and liquor to sway voters, urging them to support AAP for a better future.
title: In show of support, TMC's Shatrughan Sinha campaigns for AAP's Atishi in Delhi

description: Groundhog Punxsutawney Phil predicts six more weeks of winter after seeing his shadow today when he emerged from his den in western Pennsylvania. Ahead of the prediction today, Peta opposed the exploitation of Phil and proposed that Phil should retire and a vegan weather reveal cake should replace Phil. The proposed cake when cut would show one of two colors: blue, signifying six more weeks of winter, or pink, indicating an early spring.
title: Punxsutawney Phil sees his shadow in Groundhog Day winter prediction
Trump’s tariff gamble: 'Pain' ahead, but 'worth the price' to secure US interests

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge accused AAP chief Arvind Kejriwal of making false allegations against the Congress to defame its leaders. He credited former Delhi CM Sheila Dikshit and Sonia Gandhi for Delhi's development, stating that their efforts were responsible for the capital's progress.
title: 'Trying to defame us': Kharge targets Kejriwal, credits Sheila Dikshit Delhi's progress

description: Abhishek Sharma impressed at Mumbai's Wankhede Stadium by scoring the second-fastest century by an Indian in T20Is, reaching 100 off just 37 balls with five fours and ten sixes. Abhishek's hundred came in just 10.1 overs, surpassing Quinton de Kock's previous record. The feat also made Abhishek the third-fastest ever to the hundred-run mark in T20 internationals.
title: Abhishek fires second fastest ton by an Indian in T20Is
After Himanta spoils 'Udta Assam Party', Manipur CM voices support

description: Himanshu Sangwan dismisses Virat Kohli for six runs in an eventful over during a Ranji Trophy match at Arun Jaitley Stadium. Despite his brief homecoming, Kohli’s dismissal became a highlight, with Sangwan’s performance earning applause and recognition. Sangwan expresses his gratitude for the support and mentorship he's received, aspiring to play Test cricket for India.
title: Himanshu Sangwan: 'Ya to Krishna ji ke do maa aur baap the, ya mere hain'

description: CPI(M) leaders M V Govindan and E P Jayarajan condemned the Union Budget 2025-26 for ignoring Kerala's key demands and accused the Centre of discriminating against the state. They criticized Union Minister of State George Kurian’s remarks suggesting Kerala declare itself backward to receive more funds.
title: 'Declare Kerala backward if you want funds': Minister's remark sparks controversy
Former UK PM Rishi Sunak plays cricket in Mumbai
How 'unique walking style' caught on CCTV led cops in search of burglar

description: Delhi Police assured strict legal action against men who attacked AAP's campaign van and tore down posters. Arvind Kejriwal accused Union Home Minister Amit Shah of orchestrating the incident. AAP MLA Mohinder Goyal was assaulted during a rally and hospitalized. AAP MP Sanjay Singh blamed BJP for the violence, citing frustration over impending election loss.
title: Kejriwal says AAP van attacked; Delhi Police request formal complaint

description: Union minister Suresh Gopi sparked controversy by suggesting that the tribal affairs ministry should be managed by individuals from upper castes. He argued for the appointment of non-tribal leaders to improve tribal welfare, prompting backlash from opposition and tribal leaders for his remarks.
title: 'Members of upper castes should handle tribal affairs portfolio': Suresh Gopi

description: Three individuals were arrested by Pune police for allegedly offering MPSC exam aspirants the question paper for Rs 40 lakh. No evidence of the paper being leaked was found. Authorities recovered a list of 24 students targeted by the accused. The case is under further investigation, involving relevant sections of the Bharatiya Nyay Sanhita and the Maharashtra Competitive Exam Act.
title: MPSC aspirants get phone calls offering exam paper for Rs 40 lakh

description: India's finance minister, Nirmala Sitharaman, outlines plans for fiscal consolidation, infrastructure investment, and economic growth amidst global challenges. Fiscal deficit targets are set with a focus on reducing debt, boosting manufacturing through 'Make in India', and enhancing digital economy strategies to support sustained growth.
title: Nirmala Sitharaman on India's fiscal roadmap, growth plans & global challenges

description: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman emphasized India's consistent fiscal discipline despite not securing a rating upgrade from Moody's, which maintained India at “Baa3” with a stable outlook. She highlighted the government's commitment to debt reduction, balancing fiscal prudence, and continued public spending on key sectors.
title: 'Unblemished track record': FM Sitharaman on why Moody's has not changed India's ranking

description: Samajwadi Party MP Awadhesh Prasad condemned the brutal murder of a Dalit girl in Uttar Pradesh, accusing the state government of failing to deliver justice. The girl's mutilated body was discovered in a field, prompting an emotional response from Prasad, who vowed to resign if justice was not served. Police have detained a suspect and formed special investigation teams.
title: Watch: Samajwadi MP breaks down over murder of Dalit girl in Ayodhya

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi praised the Union Budget as the most middle-class-friendly in India's history, highlighting significant tax relief for those earning up to Rs 12 lakh. He criticized the Aam Aadmi Party for corruption and false promises, while emphasizing the BJP’s commitment to welfare measures and development.
title: 'Every family happy': PM Modi hails Union Budget as 'middle class friendly'

description: The Finance Minister has adjusted tax slabs for the middle class in the new tax regime, offering greater savings and tax rebates. Additionally, changes include enhancements in TDS limits, updated rules for self-occupied properties, and easier tax return corrections.
title: Budget 2025: 10 things individual taxpayers should know

description: Congress leaders Sonia Gandhi, Rahul Gandhi, and Priyanka Gandhi Vadra face a complaint over alleged disrespectful remarks about President Droupadi Murmu. The BJP demands an apology, accusing them of insulting the President and marginalized communities. The case is set to be heard in a Bihar court on 10 February.
title: Complaint filed against Sonia, Rahul, and Priyanka Gandhi over remarks on President Murmu

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi criticised the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) ahead of Delhi’s elections, accusing it of falling apart due to internal defections. He expressed confidence in BJP forming the next government, following several AAP leaders joining the BJP. Modi also praised the recently announced Union Budget, highlighting tax relief for the middle class.
title: Jhaadu ke tinke bikhar rahe hain,' says PM Modi on AAP leaders quitting party

description: Shein has returned to the Indian market through a new app launched by Reliance Retail, focusing on local manufacturing and strict data sovereignty. The move comes as Shein plans a potential London stock market listing and faces increased regulatory scrutiny in Europe.
title: Reliance brings app that made Zara and H&M ‘change’ their strategy to India

description: An elderly couple, Raghavan (92) and Bharatiyamma (90), were found charred in their Alappuzha home after their son, Vijayan (60), allegedly set the house on fire. Police arrested Vijayan, who confessed to the crime, citing a property dispute and the difficulty of caring for his parents. He was reportedly intoxicated during the incident.
title: Elderly couple charred to death in Kerala, 60-year-old son held

description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau urged citizens to support domestic products in response to US President Donald Trump's tariffs on Canadian goods. Trudeau highlighted the negative impacts of these tariffs and stressed the importance of unity between the two nations. Provincial leaders and the public also expressed strong opposition to the US decision.
title: 'Canadian rye over Kentucky bourbon, stay in Canada': Trudeau after US tariffs

description: OpenAI's CEO Sam Altman admitted that the company has been too secretive about its AI technology. While he supports greater transparency, it's not OpenAI's top priority. Competitors like DeepSeek are thriving with open-source strategies, challenging established firms to balance intellectual property protection with collaborative innovation. This shift could reshape the competitive landscape in AI development.
title: DeepSeek 'divides' OpenAI: Altman says, 'we have been on the wrong... '

description: India clinched a commanding nine-wicket victory over South Africa, defending their Women’s U19 T20 World Cup title. Restricting South Africa to 82 all out, India chased down the target in 11.2 overs. Key performances included Gongadi Trisha's 44 not out and a standout spell of 3/15, securing back-to-back titles for India’s U19 team.
title: India crush SA to defend U19 Women's T20 WC title

description: Actor Ram Kapoor lost 55 kilos through a sustainable approach. He emphasizes the importance of changing one's mindset for lifelong health instead of relying on temporary diets. Kapoor advises eating only two meals a day and avoiding food after sunset. His weight loss journey highlights the significance of gradual, consistent progress and overall well-being.
title: Ram Kapoor reveals how he lost 55kg, shares diet habit he adopted

description: China has strongly opposed Donald Trump's decision to impose 10% tariffs on Chinese goods and warned of countermeasures to protect its rights. China also plans to file a complaint with the WTO, arguing that such unilateral tariffs violate international trade rules and disrupt economic cooperation.
title: 'Strongly dissatisfied': China 'firmly opposes' new US tariffs, vows 'countermeasures'

description: Nasiruddin Ahmed, a senior legislator from Kaliganj, Nadia, and a Trinamool Congress member, died of cardiac arrest on Sunday. He experienced health issues late Saturday night and was taken to Palasi Hospital, where he passed away. Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee expressed her condolences, highlighting Ahmed's contributions as a trusted politician and lawyer.
title: Veteran TMC MLA Nasiruddin Ahmed dies of cardiac arrest in West Bengal

description: The BJP has launched its fourth campaign song, 'Dil valo ki Delhi ko ab BJP Sarkar chahiye', for the upcoming Delhi Assembly elections. BJP leaders praised the Union Budget as a 'golden budget'. MP Manoj Tiwari highlighted the exemption of income tax on earnings up to Rs 12 lakh, benefiting the middle class.
title: 'Delhi ko ab BJP sarkar chahiye': New campaign song 3 days ahead of polls

description: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced significant tax relief in the Union Budget, raising the nil-tax threshold to Rs 12 lakh, relieving nearly 1 crore taxpayers. She also extended the time frame for filing updated returns to 48 months. The changes signify the government's response to middle-class concerns and aim to ease bureaucratic hurdles in taxing regimes.
title: FM Nirmala describes Budget 2025 as 'by the people, for the people, of the people'

description: India clinched their second T20 World Cup title in 2024, defeating South Africa by seven runs in a thrilling final. Rohit Sharma's team remained undefeated throughout the tournament, with impressive performances in batting, bowling, and fielding. The victory marked India's first ICC trophy since 2013.
title: 'It took a while to realize': Rohit Sharma on India's T20 World Cup victory
Union Budget 2025: Gains and pains for taxpayers

description: The body of a 22-year-old Dalit woman, missing since Thursday, was found in a canal near her village in Uttar Pradesh's Ayodhya with deep wounds, fractures, and missing eyes. Her family alleges murder, criticizing police inaction. A large crowd demands justice as police investigate the case, awaiting post-mortem results to identify those responsible.
title: Dalit woman missing for 2 days found dead in desolate canal in UP
Five Nepalese returning from Maha Kumbh killed as SUV flips trying to save biker

description: Tech giants Amazon and Microsoft announced layoffs affecting multiple divisions, while SEBI took action against financial influencers for misleading advice. Nvidia faced a significant market value drop due to Chinese AI app DeepSeek. In other updates, Zoho's Sridhar Vembu steps down as CEO, and Apple released its iOS 18.3 update with improved features.
title: Nvidia's $500bn loss, layoffs at Microsoft & Amazon, & more tech news of week

description: President Trump signed an order imposing tariffs on imports from Mexico, Canada, and China, potentially affecting the global economy. Economists warn that these tariffs could worsen inflation and increase prices for goods like food, fuel, and cars in the US. Additionally, steel and other products may become more expensive.
title: Prices to rise in US after Trump imposes tariff 'to protect Americans'

description: Arvind Kejriwal, chief of Aam Aadmi Party, wrote to the Election Commission of India alleging that AAP volunteers are being harassed and intimidated by BJP workers and Delhi Police. He highlighted multiple incidents where party workers were detained on baseless charges or assaulted, including an attack on his convoy.
title: 'BJP workers, Delhi Police harassing AAP volunteers': Kejriwal writes to EC

description: Pakistan selectors announced the squad for the upcoming Champions Trophy slated to start on February 19. The squad sees the return of top-order batter Fakhar Zaman, while Saim Ayub misses out due to injury. Former captain Wasim Akram shared his views on the squad and congratulated PCB for preparing the stadiums in record time.
title: 'Bowling average 100 ki, batting average 9 ki': Akram on Pak CT squad

description: Reboots have become a staple in Hollywood, driven by commercial viability, risk mitigation, and nostalgia's potent influence. While superhero films like Superman and Spider-Man thrive, others falter due to high expectations and poor execution. The rise of streaming platforms offers creative freedom, exemplified by successful series like Daredevil, Wednesday, among others, reshaping audience engagement.
title: Reboots on repeat: Why Hollywood keeps revisiting past films & series

description: Royal Rumble 2025 was monumental with Charlotte Flair winning the Women's Royal Rumble and Jey Uso triumphing in the Men's match. DIY retained the WWE Tag Team Championship in a thrilling 2-Out-Of-3 Falls match, and Cody Rhodes overcame Kevin Owens in a brutal Ladder Match to retain the WWE Undisputed Title. A night of spectacular surprises and intense battles.
title: WWE Royal Rumble: Full winners list, top performers, matches, results and more

description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau announced 25% tariffs on $155 billion in US imports, retaliating against Donald Trump's new tariffs on imports from Canada, Mexico, and China. Additionally, Trudeau stated that duties on $30 billion worth of US alcohol and fruit will begin Tuesday, aligning with the implementation of US tariffs.
title: 25% for 25%: Canada to put tariffs on US imports in retaliation for Trump tariffs

description: In Gujarat's Dang district, five pilgrims were killed and 17 others seriously injured when a bus plunged into a 35-feet-deep gorge near Saputara hill station. The accident occurred around 4.15 am after the driver lost control. The bus was en route from Trimbakeshwar, Maharashtra to Dwarka, Gujarat, carrying 48 pilgrims from Madhya Pradesh.
title: 5 pilgrims killed, several injured as bus falls into gorge in Gujarat
Goodie morning, India: FM's 'detax diet' brings bonanza for middle class

description: Kinnar Akhada removed Mamta Kulkarni and Laxmi Narayan Tripathi from Mahamandaleshwar roles due to internal conflicts. Kulkarni faced backlash for her past in films and criminal allegations. She denied bribery allegations and emphasized her financial struggles. Kulkarni recited mantras to show her spiritual commitment, avoiding direct responses about her Vedic studies.
title: Mamta Kulkarni denies paying Rs 10cr to become Mahamandaleshwar of Kinnar Akhara

description: Rohit Sharma's forgetful nature, although often humorously recounted by his teammates, is notably endearing. During the BCCI awards, Rohit confessed that his wife might have more insights into his forgetfulness, which he chooses to keep private.
title: 'Wife will be watching': What Rohit refused to reveal to Smriti - Watch

description: The 2025 Men's Royal Rumble featured numerous surprises and intense moments, including John Cena's and AJ Styles' returns. Ultimately, Jey Uso emerged victorious after eliminating John Cena, with other key eliminations by stars like Roman Reigns and CM Punk shaping the match's dynamic outcome.
title: WWE Royal Rumble results: Jey Uso wins men's match

description: Deva's Hindi debut directed by Rosshan Andrrews features Shahid Kapoor and Pooja Hegde, earning Rs 11.37 crore in its opening weekend. The film follows ACP Dev Ambre, a hot-headed cop who loses his memory while investigating a murder. Despite mixed reviews, Shahid Kapoor's performance receives praise.
title: Deva box office collection day 2: Film collects Rs 11 crore in two days

description: Vasant Panchami, marking the onset of spring and honoring Goddess Saraswati, will be celebrated on February 2, 2025. People wear yellow clothes, prepare sweets, and engage in cultural activities. The  shubh muhurat for rituals is from 07:09 am to 12:35 pm. This day signifies new beginnings in education and the arts, celebrating wisdom and creativity.
title: Happy Basant Panchami 2025: Best messages, quotes, wishes and images

description: Controversy surrounds pacer Harshit Rana's concussion substitution for Shivam Dube during the fourth T20I between India and England, with former players questioning the decision's fairness. Notably, Ravichandran Ashwin and Zaheer Khan argue that Ramandeep Singh would have been a more appropriate replacement, urging review of concussion rules by cricket authorities.
title: 'Did we forget that it was an int'l match?': Ashwin on Rana's substitution

description: Legendary cricketer Sachin Tendulkar was honored with the Col. CK Nayudu Lifetime Achievement Award at the BCCI Awards 2025. Tendulkar advised young players to stay focused and value their opportunities, emphasizing the importance of responsibility in advancing their careers and the nation's reputation in cricket.
title: Sachin Tendulkar urges Indian cricketers not to get 'distracted' - Watch

description: Former Pakistan captain Rashid Latif criticises the squad for the Champions Trophy 2025 as a 'political selection,' questioning the inclusion of Faheem Ashraf due to his lack of recent performance. Latif highlights concerns over Pakistan's bowling attack, while former bowler Tanvir Ahmed calls the squad a 'joke,' accusing the selectors of favoritism.
title: 'A political selection; a joke': Ex-cricketers slam Pakistan's CT squad

description: England's dissatisfaction over India's 15-run win in the fourth T20I sets a charged atmosphere for the final match. Jos Buttler criticized the decision to allow a non like-for-like concussion substitute, while India looks to address form issues of key players Sanju Samson and Surya Kumar Yadav.
title: 'Concussion-sub' fire rages as India seek 4-1 scoreline against England

description: Cody Rhodes retained the WWE Undisputed Championship against Kevin Owens in a brutal ladder match. The match featured high-risk moves, with Rhodes ultimately overcoming Owens after an intense fight involving ladders and a dramatic reversal at the announce table.
title: WWE Royal Rumble 2025 ladder match results: Cody Rhodes retains title

description: The Women's Royal Rumble 2025 saw intense competition with unexpected returns and shocking eliminations. Key highlights include Alexa Bliss and Nikki Bella's surprise entries, Nia Jax's dominant eight eliminations, and Charlotte Flair's triumphant victory after eliminating Roxanne Perez and Nia Jax. The energetic atmosphere and stunning performances captivated the WWE Universe throughout the match.
title: WWE royal rumble match result: The queen Charlotte Flair wins women's category

description: FM Nirmala Sitharaman is pushing for deregulation and ease of doing business, aiming to cut red tape significantly. The Jan Vishwas Bill 2.0 will decriminalize over 100 provisions, and a high-level committee will review non-financial regulations. The government also plans to improve customs classifications and international taxation processes.
title: How business friendly is your state? Check invest index

description: Opposition leaders criticized the BJP government's Budget, labeling it as lacking innovation and failing to address key economic issues like stagnant wages and a complex GST system. Rahul Gandhi called it a superficial fix, while former FM Chidambaram and others commented on its focus on wooing specific voter groups rather than driving substantial economic change.
title: No new ideas, band-aid for bullet wounds: Rahul Gandhi on Union Budget

description: Security and crowd management efforts have been intensified at the ghats in Prayagraj for the Basant Panchami sacred bathing ritual, expected to attract 4 to 5 crore devotees. Measures include strict route plans, paramilitary presence, and reinforced barricades to prevent overcrowding after the tragic stampede on Jan 29.
title: Security tightened for first Amrit snan after Maha Kumbh stampede

description: Former India spinner Ravichandran Ashwin humorously shared his post-retirement experience at the BCCI Naman Awards 2025. He spoke about enjoying family time, reminisced about playing alongside Sachin Tendulkar, and confirmed his preparation for the upcoming IPL season with Chennai Super Kings. Ashwin retired with 765 wickets and 4,394 runs in his stellar career.
title: 'They just kicked me out!': Ashwin's hilarious take on retirement

description: Pune civic health authorities are investigating if lapses in water chlorination contributed to the surge in Guillain-Barré Syndrome (GBS) cases, linked to diarrhoea preceding GBS symptoms. They are testing water and meat samples for bacterial contamination, including Campylobacter jejuni and norovirus, to identify the source of the outbreak.
title: Did chlorination lapses lead to Guillain-Barré Syndrome (GBS) in people?

description: A 20-year-old MBBS student, Ivy Prasad, was found hanging in her room at Kamarhati ESI Hospital quarters. Her mother, a doctor, discovered her after multiple unanswered calls. No suicide note was found, and police have registered a case of unnatural death. Authorities suspect depression; an investigation is underway, and a post-mortem is being conducted.
title: RG Kar MBBS student found hanging in hospital quarters, cops suspect depression

description: A 21-year-old woman from Memnagar has accused her husband of blackmail and online harassment, alleging he leaked her private photos and videos on social media after she sought a divorce. Distressed by the threats and social media humiliation, she approached Ghatlodia police, leading to a case of defamation and criminal intimidation against him.
title: Gujarat man leaks wife’s private photos, videos after she seeks divorce

description: Seven students from a government school in Harur, Dharmapuri fell ill after eating lunch that contained a dead lizard. The incident led to the suspension of three cooks involved in the noon-meal scheme. The students' condition is stabilizing, while an inquiry was conducted by education officials. Prompt action by teachers prevented further consumption of the contaminated food.
title: Dead lizard found in lunch served at govt school in Tamil Nadu; 7 students fall ill

description: Gulf Giants secured a seven-wicket victory over Abu Dhabi Knight Riders in the ILT20, climbing to third place in the standings. Gerhard Erasmus and Tom Curran led the chase, while Shimron Hetmyer provided the finishing touch. The Knight Riders struggled, with only David Willey’s 41 standing out, ultimately posting 123/7 in 20 overs.
title: ILT20: Gulf Giants stay alive in playoff race, beat Abu Dhabi Knight Riders

description: Durban's Super Giants won against Joburg Super Kings by 11 runs via DLS at the Wanderers, finishing their Season 3 on a high. Heinrich Klaasen's 76 not out and Wiaan Mulder's 30 not out helped DSG to 173/4. Despite Donovan Ferreira's quick 51, DSG's Pretorius secured the win. JSK will face Sunrisers Eastern Cape in the Eliminator.
title: SA20: Durban end season on high with thrilling DLS win over Joburg

description: US President Donald Trump announces substantial tariffs on Canada, Mexico, and China, citing threats from illegal immigration and drug trafficking. These tariffs include a 25% levy on imports from Canada and Mexico. Economists warn of significant economic disruptions and potential price increases for American consumers.
title: Trump imposes sweeping tariffs on Canada, Mexico and China

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman's Budget speech announced tax exemption for salaries up to Rs 12 lakh, leading to applause and chants of 'Modi, Modi' in the BJP benches. However, opposition parties protested over the Kumbh stampede and eventually walked out. The session, marked by divided reactions, reflected the political split and customary reactions in the 75-minute address.
title: Union Budget 2025: FM's 'tax teaser' lightens mood in House

description: Commerce, MSME and finance ministries in India will collaborate to identify key sectors needing significant capital for technology upgrades, marketing, and accessing new markets to boost exports. An Export Promotion Mission with a budget of Rs 2,250 crore has been announced to facilitate export credit and support MSMEs in overcoming non-tariff measures in foreign markets.
title: Union Budget 2025: MSMEs get Rs 2,250 crore booster shot with mission exports

description: Europe's largest chip company ASML views the emergence of China's DeepSeek as a positive, despite initial market jitters. CEO Christophe Fouquet highlights the benefits of cost-efficient AI models, emphasizing the broader potential for AI-related chip demand across various applications, rather than just large model training.
title: Why CEO of Europe's biggest chip company thinks DeepSeek 'American problem'

description: A 21-year-old software engineer, Aiyaz Shemale, was crushed to death by a truck after his motorcycle hit a pothole in Bhiwandi, resulting in him losing balance. The police have booked the truck driver for negligence following their investigation, although the truck driver fled the scene.
title: Techie returning from pal’s birthday mowed down as bike hits pothole in Bhidwandi

description: A 25-year-old man, Nikesh Shinde, allegedly murdered his former girlfriend, Jagruti Satve, by slashing her throat at her home in New Panvel. After the attack, he attempted suicide but survived and is now recuperating in the hospital. The police reported that the man was upset over their breakup and suspected her of seeing another man.
title: 25-year-old man kills ex-lover over break-up, tries to kill himself in Navi Mumbai
